commitResults.messageBody:
Parser class have some unintended and potential mistake could not be
noticed due to user invalid input. (e.g. mark number out of list).

Adding assert code on every necessarily needs part preventing from this
issue. For example, assert rest commands length to check whether it
matches the required input.

Although previous code had already handled this issue, this week's iP
project required to do so.

https://nus-cs2103-ay2324s2.github.io/website

commitResults.messageTitle: Modify most of classes to have a hierarchy structure
commitResults.messageBody:
For example, the original packages only have two which is Ping and
Command. Renamed them with lower case to fit the standard of commit
then separate all of them into 4 different packages which are
command, exceptions, GUI, job, and a package folder for checking
time.

Implement a better design GUI to make the window more beautiful and
tidy.

A good and comfortable window will improve the user experience. So,
doing a GUI beauty improvement is necessary.

Let's
* change the font to make chatbot and user different
* add different background colors to distinguish chatbot and user
Modify most of classes to have a hierarchy structure
